|------|-------|-------|--------|-------------|----------|
| Dashboard | /dashboard | foundation | shell | Navigation hub | keep |
| Repair Create | /repair/create | core | shell + pattern | Primary loop input | create |
| Repair List | /repair/list | supporting | shell + pattern | Demo credibility | create |

## Entity Mapping

| Entity | Fields | Storage | Notes |
|--------|--------|---------|-------|
| Repair request | id, description, category, handler, status | in-memory dict | seeded on startup |

## Field Mapping

| UI Field | Data Field | Type | Required | Validation |
|----------|------------|------|----------|------------|
| description | description | string | yes | max 500 chars |
| category | category | string | no | from workflow output |
| handler | handler | string | no | from workflow output |

## Generated Files Plan

| File | Action | Source | Purpose |
|------|--------|--------|---------|
| app.py | modify | shell | add repair routes and workflow endpoint |
| templates/repair/create.html | create | business-requirement | primary loop input form |
| templates/repair/list.html | create | business-requirement | list submitted requests |

## Workflow Mock Contract

\`\`\`json
{
  "request": { "input": "string" },
  "response": { "ok": true, "data": { "category": "string", "handler": "string" }, "error": null, "fallback": true }
}
\`\`\`

## Data Storage Decision

| Store | Why Enough For V1 | Reset / Seed Strategy | Upgrade Path |
|-------|-------------------|-----------------------|--------------|
| in-memory dict | Local demo only | seed in app.py | SQLite or JSON file |

## Changed Decisions

| Decision | Original Plan | Changed To | Reason |
|----------|---------------|------------|--------|
| - | - | - | - |

## Known Limits

- Prototype only.
`,
    'docs/workflow-integration.md': `# Workflow Integration

## Role
The AI workflow classifies repair requests and returns a suggested action.

## Business Workflow Endpoint

\`POST /api/repairs/triage\`

## Adapter Location
\`workflow_adapter.py\`

## Request Shape
\`\`\`json
{ "input": "string" }
\`\`\`

## Response Shape
\`\`\`json
{ "ok": true, "data": { "category": "string", "handler": "string" }, "error": null, "fallback": true }
\`\`\`

## Mock Fallback
When the AI platform is unavailable, the app returns a mock response with the same shape.

## Error Handling
| Scenario | Behavior |
|----------|----------|
| Invalid input | Return 400 with error envelope and code INVALID_INPUT |
| Timeout | Return mock fallback and log warning |
| Empty result | Return success envelope with empty flag |
| Platform error | Return mock fallback with same shape and log error |

## Configuration
| Name | Default | Purpose |
|------|---------|---------|
| WORKFLOW_MOCK | true | Use mock response |
| WORKFLOW_TIMEOUT | 10 | Real call timeout |

## Switching to Real Workflow
Set WORKFLOW_MOCK=false and implement _call_real_workflow.

## Test Examples
\`\`\`bash
curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:5000/api/repairs/triage -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"input":"楼道灯坏了"}'
\`\`\`
`,
    'docs/test-report.md': `# Test Report

## Test Scope
